      "schema:description": "Artistic and epistemological concept formulated by Alexandre Mury within the A.M.O. ontology. The Self-Implicative Method designates the practice through which the artist critically intervenes in the contemporary regimes of existence of their own work, recognizing that documentation, cataloguing, circulation, ontologies, metadata, and algorithmic systems no longer merely describe the artwork, but actively participate in its historicity, recoverability, and public intelligibility.",
